                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.93/334: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-08-28T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 28, 1936—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>210. Reference your 415, August 25, 1 p.m. Department’s 204, August 22, 1 p.m.,
                    was for your information and guidance and should not be construed as implying
                    anything not stated in its text. It gives you in the first three numbered
                    paragraphs new and latest information and was occasioned by the developments
                    reported in its paragraph 1 and in the fifth and following words of its
                    paragraph 3. Please reread carefully, especially first sentence of paragraph 3
                    and last sentence of paragraph 4, the latter of which sentences applies to all
                    that precedes it in that telegram. See also Department’s 209, August 28, 4
                    p.m.</p>
                <p>Department is glad to have all the information given in your telegram under
                    reference.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
